  <div class="topic">
    <h4>HTML Tags and Elements</h4>
    <p>HTML is made up of HTML "attributes". Each "attribute" is made up of an "opening tag" and a "closing tag". Below is an example of the tags that make up a "paragraph" or "p" element.</p>

    <img src="http://www.elevationacademy.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Screen-Shot-2016-02-25-at-1.18.12-PM.png">
    <img src="http://www.elevationacademy.co/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Screen-Shot-2016-02-25-at-1.18.29-PM.png">

    <p>Below we have a "paragraph element". The element is made up of the opening tag, the text in the middle and the closing tag.</p>

    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">p</span>></span>Hey I'm a paragraph element!<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">p</span>></span>
</pre>

    <p>How many elements are in the code below? What are their tags?</p>
    <pre style="background:#000;color:#f8f8f8"><span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
  <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">h1</span>></span>All About HTML<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">h1</span>></span>
  <span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;<span style="color:#89bdff">p</span>></span>I'm in a div and it's great.<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">p</span>></span>
<span style="color:#89bdff">&lt;/<span style="color:#89bdff">div</span>></span>
</pre>

